-- Huadian Energy to Acquire Power Company in Heilongjiang for $57.5 Million
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-15T00:08:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/huadian-energy-to-acquire-power-company-in-heilongjiang-for-57-5-million.html

          
          
             Huadian Energy Co. plans to pay
389.4 million yuan to acquire a Chinese power company in the
northeastern province of Heilongjiang from Qiqihaer Xinbao
Heating & Power Co. and Singapore-based Asia Power Corporation
Ltd., according to a statement to the Shanghai Stock Exchange.  
 Huadian expects a 148 million yuan loss in the first half
on a surge in coal prices, the Chinese electric company said in
a separate statement.  
